        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 8:08PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 808 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Waco, or near Buchanan.
This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Buchanan, Bremen, Tallapoosa, Mount Zion, Waco, and Bowdon Junction.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
